Golang installation
--------------------

1. Check for latest stable Golang Linux version at https://go.dev/dl/

2. As root, do, wget https://go.dev/dl/go1.21.0.linux-amd64.tar.gz

3. As root, tar -C /usr/local -xzf go1.21.0.linux-amd64.tar.gz

4. Go should be installed at, /usr/local/go/bin/go. To find go binary, adjust PATH as, export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin

GoLang uninstallation
----------------------

1. As root, rm -rf /usr/local/go

How KMIPCLI is built?
----------------------

The source of our KMIPCLI can be found at vaultcli/kmipcli in htdc repo.

The Makefile at kmipcli/Makefile does the following,

1. Creates a temporary Go workspace at vaultcli/kmipcli-build
2. Copies all required files and packages from vaultcli to vaultcli/kmipcli and copies the soucre code to the src/ directory of tmp workspace(vaultcli/kmipcli-build). 
3. Run commands to create go mod and go sums files to download required packages.
4. Required Linux & Windows binaries are compiled & built at vaultcli/kmipcli-build/bin directory. Note that these for amd64 architecture systems.